ributed automatically each day. The timing … is a coincidence of the worst kind, and we apologise for any distress or upset caused by what might seem to be a highly insensitive choice. What we hope to show with our words of the day is that even seemingly commonplace words can have interesting etymologies; however we have taken today's word down from the OED online homepage and are now taking immediate steps to review our scheduling and selection policy.&quot;</p><p></p><p>Twitter users have taken the apology with good grace. &quot;Personally, no apology is necessary. I found the linguistic analysis a much-needed step back from the recent horror,&quot; said one. &quot;Thanks for the response. Relieved to hear it was an unfortunate coincidence and not intentional,&quot; wrote another. A third said: &quot;Hard to believe some people would Tweet to @OEDonline abt their unfortunate Word of the Day, but not the @NRA. Priorities people!&quot;</p><!-- Guardian Watermark: internal-code/content/401385747|2012-12-22T11:49:02Z|06cb836bc0aefee06154d7aa0ea92478434c5dbd -->","showInRelatedContent":"true","lastModified":"2012-12-20T12:53:22Z","hasStoryPackage":"true","score":"1.0","secureThumbnail":"https://static-secure.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Arts/Arts_/Pictures/2012/12/20/1356005600716/A-man-reads-a-copy-of-the-005.jpg","standfirst":"Choosing 'bloodbath' as word of the day so soon after Sandy Hook shootings was 'coincidence of worst kind', says OED","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/3ck4m","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Arts/Arts_/Pictures/2012/12/20/1356005600716/A-man-reads-a-copy-of-the-005.jpg","wordcount":"314","commentable":"true","internalContentCode":"401385747","internalOctopusCode":"7049300","isPremoderated":"false","byline":"Alison Flood","publication":"guardian.co.uk","internalPageCode":"1845229","shouldHideAdverts":"true","liveBloggingNow":"false","commentCloseDate":"2012-12-27T12:11:00Z"},"tags":[{"id":"books/books","type":"keyword","sectionId":"books","s